SIMPLE: underbelly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underbelly
<hw>Un"der*bel`ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
lower ventral part of the abdomen of an animal, especially one that
walks on four feet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The surface of an object closest to the ground,
especially of an extended object such as an airplane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The weak point of an object vulnerable to attack;
used especially in the phrase ⟦ldquo⟧the soft
<ex>underbelly</ex>⟦rdquo⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underbid</ent>⟦br⟧
